<h2>Project Idea</h2>
<br><br><br><br>

<h3>Overview</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>
        <h4>Topic</h4>
        <p>Telkom+ purpose is to create a connectivity towards “non-smart” devices that aren’t able to connect directly to the internet. We supply an application and a device that allows these “non-smart” devices become smart devices with a simple plug-and-play adaptor, once doing so clients are able to connect “non-smart” and already available smart devices to the Telkom+ app that grants them access to a variety of controls for these devices. Basic controls include the ability to switch the device on and off using the app or accessing CCTV footage, but more advanced controls include the ability to connect CCTV and motion sensors to a lock down mode if there is movement inside without a member having the application connected. We want our users to have the complete freedom to control and connect devices for a better lifestyle, giving them no restraint to which device can or can’t connect to their application, but rather encouraging them to connect “non-smart” devices.</p>
        <p>The main proposal that our project tries to provide, is an application that will help organise the wide variety of smart devices that are currently available.  With the ever-growing market of smart technology, household appliances today are becoming more and more feature rich and their capabilities are higher than previous non internet capable versions of themselves. The ability to streamline them all within a simple, user friendly interface is what our main goals are.</p>
        <p>The expected outcome is to support the growth of smart technology. With the developments of required technology, such as sensors and faster internet, becoming cheaper and more accessible they more people are incorporating smart appliances into their daily lives. As more people become more accustomed to things being on demand and ready when they need it, the demand for smart technology rises and the need to be able to control them.</p>
        </li>
        <br>
        <li>
        <h4>Motivation</h4>
        <p></p>
        </li>
        <br>
        <li>
        <h4>Landscape</h4>
        <p></p>
        </li>
    </ul>

